    <div class="prose">
      <div class="te-block">
        <p>Esophagectomy (food pipe removal and reconstruction) surgical oncology లో most complex procedures లో ఒకటి. Chest మరియు abdomen రెండూ involve అవుతాయి. Specialist training అవసరం.</p>
        <p>నేను Journal of Minimal Access Surgery (2021) లో MIE పైన publish చేశాను. Charité Berlin లో advanced training లో MIE technique extensively practice చేశాను. Laparoscopic abdominal phase + thoracoscopic chest phase combination better recovery ఇస్తుంది.</p>
        <p>Important point: esophageal cancer కి surgery alone sufficient కాదు. CROSS trial (multimodal chemoradiation before surgery) standard of care establish చేసింది. నేను Tumor Board లో neoadjuvant chemoradiation plan తో surgery combine చేస్తాను.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="en-block">
        <p>Esophagectomy (food pipe removal and reconstruction) is one of the most complex procedures in surgical oncology. It involves both chest and abdomen and requires specialist training.</p>
        <p>I published on MIE in the Journal of Minimal Access Surgery (2021). During my advanced training at Charité Berlin, I practised the MIE technique extensively. The combination of laparoscopic abdominal phase plus thoracoscopic chest phase gives better recovery outcomes.</p>
        <p>Important point: surgery alone is not sufficient for oesophageal cancer. The CROSS trial established multimodal chemoradiation before surgery as the standard of care. I combine neoadjuvant chemoradiation with surgery, planned at the Tumor Board.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
